‚ÄúI love anything that haunts me...and never leaves.‚Äù 

Buckley on repeat and rare sunshine getting me through.  I can‚Äôt shake this record lately‚Ä¶20 yrs since the last time I was obsessively haunted by these songs, and for whatever reason it‚Äôs all I want to listen to these days. 

Grace is the kind of record that makes me believe real records are still worth believing in and making‚Ä¶and I guess I‚Äôve been needing to wrap myself in grace more than usual lately anyway. We all do.

‚ÄúI have no advice for anybody; except to, you know, be awake enough to see where you are at any given time, and how that is beautiful, and has poetry inside. Even places you hate.‚Äù J.Buckley

(And before you give me shit about smoking‚Ä¶just testing fake herbal cigarettes for a shoot. 
Smoking while listening to Jeff feels right anyway.  Muy 90‚Äôs. Muy angst. Muy me.)

I can‚Äôt wait to share these conversations with you! Unknowing Season Two will begin airing March 2022.

latestPosts.caption:
My album Me Veo is out in the world today, and I‚Äôm feeling everything all at once, but mostly overwhelming gratitude.

Three years ago I left the life I knew and leapt into the unknown with nothing but my instincts guiding me‚Ä¶and it was a time of deep and soulful reckoning.  In that quiet dark, I began writing these songs‚Ä¶or maybe it‚Äôs better to say, they wrote themselves through me. I read recently that perhaps we‚Äôre not remade in the ashes, but rather revealed.  Me Veo means ‚ÄúI see myself‚Äù in Spanish, and I‚Äôm so thankful to the magic of these songs for helping me see the contours of who I‚Äôve been becoming all along with greater clarity, surrender and love.  My hope is that as you listen you see yourself mirrored too in every exhaled sigh and sung melody‚Ä¶that the resonance reveals something you recognize in yourself.

A lot of this seeing was inspired by the lines of Rainer Maria Rilke:
‚Äú I want to be with those who know secret things
or else alone.
I want to be a mirror for your whole body‚Ä¶
I want to unfold.
I don‚Äôt want to stay folded anywhere,
because where I am folded, there I am a lie.‚Äù

I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôll ever be done unfolding and unfurling‚Ä¶but this album captures a significant bloom that has been a lifetime in the making‚Ä¶and I‚Äôm really proud to share it with you today.

There are too many people to thank (so please see the liner credit slide above for the community that made this album) but I need to express my deepest gratitude to @david_vandervelde for producing this album with such care and sensitivity, and for bringing this album to life with me.  Getting to work with someone I‚Äôve known since we were teenagers, who was so deeply formative to me when I first began making music, is a gift I will never fully be able to express. I‚Äôm so glad fate wove our lives together and am so thankful our lives and creativity continue to weave new spells into this world.

I hope you all love this album as much as I poured my own love into every step of making it.  Me Veo is available through @label51recordings wherever you listen to your tunes, and on vinyl (Link in profile)

‚ÄúAn Erotic Sigh of Surrender‚Äù: Brie Stoner Premieres Her Empowering and Vulnerable Debut Album ‚ÄòMe Veo‚Äô (@briestoner)
‚Äî
Singer/songwriter Brie Stoner is empowered and emboldened on her dreamy debut album ‚ÄòMe Veo,‚Äô an achingly intimate and soul-stirring sonic blanket of self-actualization, inward connection, and spiritual release.
.
‚Äú‚ÄòMe Veo‚Äô is, I suppose, that fiat discovery of seeing myself at last in that way as a woman who is so much more than one thing, and committed to embodying a powerful vulnerability in every part of my life.‚Äù
.
‚ÄúFor so much of life I felt like I had to choose between either/or‚Äôs: Between being an artist or academic pursuits, being from Spain or being American, being fleshy and human or spiritual, being a mother or being a lover. All of that time in solitude really gave me the opportunity to begin to heal those internal rifts and come home to myself as being both/and.‚Äù
.
‚ÄúIt‚Äôs a record about discovering that everything can and does belong in me, and can harmonically co-exist in a way that feels really fulfilling and empowering. It‚Äôs one thing to discover that kind of creative clarity and make a bunch of shit‚Ä¶ but it‚Äôs another thing to discover that inexhaustible creative force and learn how to wield it in a way that makes you a more kind, loving, and joyful person.‚Äù
.
‚ÄúI started writing these songs that matched all that longing, silky sensuality and unfurling that was taking place inside me. I started writing in Spanish and French because there are just some feelings that get lost in translation.‚Äù
.
‚ÄúUltimately when we connect with a song or an album, what we‚Äôre feeling is the resonance of feeling less alone in our feelings, of being seen. So, in that way I hope this album, which is all about my learning to fully see myself, creates that mirroring for listeners to see themselves reflected as well.‚Äù
.

It‚Äôs one thing to discover that kind of creative clarity and make a bunch of shit‚Ä¶ but it‚Äôs another thing to discover that inexhaustible creative force and learn how to wield it in a way that makes you a more kind, loving, and joyful person.‚Äù
.
‚ÄúI started writing these songs that matched all that longing, silky sensuality and unfurling that was taking place inside me. I started writing in Spanish and French because there are just some feelings that get lost in translation.‚Äù
.
‚ÄúUltimately when we connect with a song or an album, what we‚Äôre feeling is the resonance of feeling less alone in our feelings, of being seen. One more day until my album Me Veo is out in the world! These songs represent the culmination of a real homecoming for me, Polaroids of every choice, heartbreak and decision that gave me the courage, permission and freedom to leave behind the safety of what I knew 3 years ago and become a full time musician and artist.  It is a reckoning of what it takes to be brave enough to really look in the mirror and face every shadow and see myself (Me Veo) for who who I am‚Ä¶and no longer shrink, hide or pretend otherwise. I cannot wait to share this album with you! Link in bio to pre-save or order your copy in Vinyl.
